Formed in 2007, Romeo Spike is a 4 piece modern rock group based in Atlanta, GA.  Their line-up features: Michael Kunz (Chicago, IL - lead vocals, Rhodes electric piano & guitar) - Donn Aaron (Pensacola FL - lead guitar, pedal steel & backing vocals) - Skyler Ross (Atlanta, GA - bass & backing vocals) and Owen Liversidge (Glastonbury, England - drums, programming & backing vocals.) The group began performing in 2009 and their debut full length album "For The Cause" was self-recorded and co-produced by Matt Still (Elton John.) In the band's first efforts to promote "For The Cause", multiple national album and show reviews have described Romeo Spike as innovative with a futuristic flair who take the best elements of yesterday and push them toward the limits of tomorrow.

Music video "Star Power": 
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4Xx_wjraRVw

extra:
Deep River Running is a collaboration that started in the Spring of 2008 between Nick Schinder and Jacqui Doherty.

Professional songwriter/singer/keyboard/guitar/producer/world citizen Nick Schinder, aka The Child (his long term project and alter ego: www.thechildmusic.co.uk) has won several contests around the world, travelled and gigged around Latin America and Europe, and released 4 albums with The Child, plus, he contributed to countless projects with his playing and songs.

Lyricist Jacqueline Doherty, aka Claudia Flaxton. Jacqueline is a published Poet with the International Society of Poets & Photographer, Diploma 04. After a number of years writing screenplays and poetry for fun, she decided to take her poems and turn them into songs. She set to work with artists that could add melody to her words, Nick being the one with whom she has worked the most, up to the point where they can now call themselves a creative duo. All songs written by Nick Schinder (music) and Jacqui Doherty (lyrics), except “Elephant & Castle” (lyrics & music by Nick Schinder)

Nick & Jacqui agree that the name Deep River Running, ''reflects well our attitude & style of music.''
Personnel: Nick Schinder: Vocals, keyboards & guitars. Jacqui Doherty: Lyrics

title: Encore
extra:
LEBOWSKI – A polish band founded in 2002, playing a wide spectrum of progressive music.

On the debut album in 2010, listener gets to experience the tunes along the lines of artistic rock, motion pictures music, experimental and improvisation, all in harmonised integrity.
“Cinematic” is music for a non-existent movie. From a theme aspect we can intrepidly consider it as a concept album, dedicated to the ‘big figures’ of the polish and world cinema.

What comes to the music – the CD is very compact, enriched with dynamic patterns, creating a self-collage. Like a picture of a good director. Lebowski holds listeners in tension, changing the moods, playing according to emotions. Complex and multidimensional compositions, are enabling a surprising and dynamic plot. The entirety is completed with rich instrumental use and the whole ensemble is an interesting arrangement, where the music isn’t held from being in some cases asthetic, modest and soft.
Lyrics for the “Cinematic” are original quotes adopted from the classical polish and international movies.

extra:
Deep River Running is a collaboration that started in the Spring of 2008 between Nick Schinder and Jacqui Doherty.

Professional songwriter/singer/keyboard/guitar/producer/world citizen Nick Schinder, aka The Child (his long term project and alter ego: www.thechildmusic.co.uk) has won several contests around the world, travelled and gigged around Latin America and Europe, and released 4 albums with The Child, plus, he contributed to countless projects with his playing and songs.

Lyricist Jacqueline Doherty, aka Claudia Flaxton. Jacqueline is a published Poet with the International Society of Poets & Photographer, Diploma 04. After a number of years writing screenplays and poetry for fun, she decided to take her poems and turn them into songs. She set to work with artists that could add melody to her words, Nick being the one with whom she has worked the most, up to the point where they can now call themselves a creative duo. All songs written by Nick Schinder (music) and Jacqui Doherty (lyrics), except “Elephant & Castle” (lyrics & music by Nick Schinder)

Nick & Jacqui agree that the name Deep River Running, ''reflects well our attitude & style of music.''
Personnel: Nick Schinder: Vocals, keyboards & guitars. Jacqui Doherty: Lyrics

extra:
Out of India to “Oz” The Journey of Rhett May
What does a cup of coffee, the Himalayan Mountains, and tracks left by creatures called “Wooly Bullys” have in common? Easy, Rhett May! So, immediately you think Bigfoot or Abominable Snowman, and huge tracks left in the snow, right? Not exactly…These Wooly Bullys did exist, and the tracks they've left behind are musical tracks. See, Rhett May is a seasoned musician whose first band was named The Wooly Bullys. He's not as elusive as the legendary Bigfoot;however,he has left musical footprints that lead out of India - to his current home in Australia, kindly known as “Oz.”
Rhett May owes his rare musical sound and style to the unique environment that he grew up in. Born in Calcutta, India, he was immersed in a magical, musical melting pot. Carnatic and Hindustani music and instruments such as the Sitar and Tabla always providing melody and percussion against a daily backdrop of lifting and soaring voices of Ragas. Ragas especially played a vital part of Rhett's musical experience with their series of five or more musical notes forming melody. However, this environment of classical Indian music wasn't the only sounds floating about Calcutta. By the time Rhett had begun boarding school in the Himalayan foothills; western music had also begun an invasion. Rolling Stones, Beatles,Cream, or Jimi Hendrix. Rhett lived the magic of the musical melting pot.Few,if any songwriters and musicians could grow up in such a perfect time and place of musical menagerie. For Rhett May Indian culture and music mixed with that from the west.
There’s no doubt Rhett May is back to music, and his latest single...'Cocktails and Cannabis' setting fire to music charts across the globe....is the harbinger of a new era in music that is unique and a breath of fresh air !!As one scribe puts it..."It's hypnotic...it's exotic...a love song with an edge that goes round and round inside your head....very Haight Ashbury "........

title: dreamer
extra:
My name is Richard Estick. I am in the photo.

I'm based in Westchester, NY. My influences are many, from Marvin Gaye and Carole King to Donny Hathaway, Tommy James and the Shondells and Curtis Mayfield and some others.
All the trax are laid in Reason software then Rewired to Logic to add the vocal.

I have been writing for a number of years now with very little real success. My excuse is is, simply, that the right ears have not heard what I do. I submit these trax to you in an effort to break the cycle. I work hard, and my hope is that you will hear something that you
consider pleasing to the ear and that will have a more than moderate impact on the market.

When you have a moment take a listen. I would welcome any critique one way or the other.
Contact me at: 223rdest@gmail.com, 203-817-4463


Sincerely,

Richard Estick

Formed in 2007, Romeo Spike is a 4 piece modern rock group based in Atlanta, GA.  Their line-up features: Michael Kunz (Chicago, IL - lead vocals, Rhodes electric piano & guitar) - Donn Aaron (Pensacola FL - lead guitar, pedal steel & backing vocals) - Skyler Ross (Atlanta, GA - bass & backing vocals) and Owen Liversidge (Glastonbury, England - drums, programming & backing vocals.) The group began performing in 2009 and their debut full length album "For The Cause" was self-recorded and co-produced by Matt Still (Elton John.) In the band's first efforts to promote "For The Cause", multiple national album and show reviews have described Romeo Spike as innovative with a futuristic flair who take the best elements of yesterday and push them toward the limits of tomorrow.

extra: Roger Dodge has been a sideman for years in numerous bands throughout Texas, Oklahoma, and Florida (in the USA). "They used to run us out of the back room at Tootsies in Ft. extra: Midwestern roots grew sideways in all directions searching landscapes and people for stories. 40 years of scratching notes and humming melodies end up here. I've never been anchored to any particular style of music, so be ready for anything. My VISIT STORE link above has a few dozen more to bend your ear. Thanks for listening.

title: U Aint Holding Me
extra: Originally from-Indianapolis, IN...No Name moved to Albuquerque, NM 5 years ago to organize his musical thoughts and platform called, "3 Verze Newz". No Name and his half-brother were raised by their mother, a single parent...Observing countless days of his mother working, and giving her all to support him and his brother was all No Name needed to see and understand how the world really worked as a kid. Watching his family grow apart, and past friends walk away, as if his opinions and leadership skills did not matter, has affected his psychological growth, while maintaining as an eccentric/artful individual who sees todays society as what he calls the "phony maze". According to No Name, it is this phony maze that is causing too many families to grow apart and seek unfocused paths, because of monetary greed. No Name's lyrical content scrapes the surface of real life issues, to the depths of political and corporate scandal, racism, religion and cultural pride. His platform is sure 2 grasp the mind of the so called intellectual, while providing poetic confidence to those who feel the system has failed them. No Name's - poetic thoughts - stem from the bases that everybody matters. He feels that Americas current state is due to false leadership, given to those who primarily have backgrounds that include monetary means, which promotes respect or fear of those who dont have a gift for leadership... No Name's societal evaluation has produced metaphorical thoughts that when blended together with "literal reality", reveal that God's soldiers are the "unappealing thugs", who fight for and speak the truth for change! Will the world listen, or continue on the very destructive path it created? With an, B.Sc. in Industrial Technology, from Ball State University, his path so far has been purely spiritual. He fears not the phony maze, but those who see the tattooed thug as a threat. Choice of words tell the real story, and most of all- "If I Have No Vision, Then Life Iz Just Talk" - No Name N.

In The Sky
extra:
"In The Sky"
Rick Britto - Matt Richard

performers:
Rick Britto - tenor saxophone
Matt Richard - piano

Recording, Mixing and Mastering by Rick Britto
Cover Design by Matt Richard
Recorded at Wheaton College on August 16, 2010
©2010 All Rights Reserved - BMI and TrineArc Music


LINER NOTES FROM RICK BRITTO:
Recorded in only a three hour session, this recent collaboration with Matt has been a labor of love. Matt and I have played in numerous ensembles for years from big band to small ensembles but, this is our first time working together in a duo setting. Matt is one of the most sensitive players I have had the opportunity to ever perform with. HIs compositions are both beautiful and poignant creations I had the pleasure to perform on this recording.
All six of my compositions on "In The Sky" are very different in style or feel and all were composed for people and places in my life's experience. "Miles Away" was written while doing more than 10 years of road travel gigging in the 1980s. In The Sky is a circular melody that never seems to end. It was actually written while I was floating in the sky of a waking lucid dream. Sometimes dreams do come true and can become real music! "Forever More" is thru-composed love song written in the jazz waltz feel. It also has lyrics which I hope to someday record with a vocalist. "Lionel" is a traditional 1940s style jazz swing ballad composed as a tribute to my first saxophone teacher and mentor, Lionel Soares, who unfortunately passed away in July 2009. Lionel had a great influence on my life in music. This composition and performance recreates Lionel's style and grace as I remember him dearly. "My Mama" is a tribute to my Mom, Evie Britto, written in the traditional Cape Verdean rhythmic style called the Coladeira. "Starry Eyed Girl" is my take on the classic tune, Star Eyes, written as a tribute to my girl friend, Kathy Crowley, who is the female vocalist that brightens the stage in performance with the folk group, Pumpkin Head Ted.

LINER NOTES FROM MATT RICHARD:
This recent collaboration with Rick Britto has been very positive. We have known each other for the past twenty years and have played together in many jazz settings, but not as a duo until now. Rick has an amazing technical capacity on the tenor saxophone but he also plays with a tremendous amount of feeling. His interpretations of each melody are unique and well conceived. Rick is also a very good jazz pianist and that kept me on my toes for this session. I appreciate his ability to not only compose and perform this project but to record and edit it as well.
I consider all five of my compositions on "In The Sky" fairly straight-ahead in form, melody, and harmony. The rhythms are based on traditional swing, Latin-American, and ballad styles with plenty of space in which can players can improvise. "Side Step" has loose connections to Lee Morgan’s composition "Ceora". It was inspired by the original introduction that I used for that song on my first CD. "Past" was originally written and set in a different key as part of a collection of duets that I wrote for the bassist Bronek Suchanek. This song and that complete duo project will hopefully be recorded someday soon. The choro rhythm of "Strait Ahead" is typically Brazilian and the feel of this song came through listening to pianist Alan Pasqua’s composition Highway as well as the music of composer and bandleader Maria Schneider. "Swingin’ At The Columns" is a tribute to two of my favorite jazz musicians of all time, Dave McKenna and Dick Johnson, who performed at a club called The Columns on Cape Cod for many years. Finally, "A Song For Semenya" was influenced by my collaborations over the years with jazz vocalist Semenya McCord. Although in meter of 3/4, it has a bit of Horace Silver’s Song For My Father and other gospel roots in it.

extra:
Deep River Running is a collaboration that started in the Spring of 2008 between Nick Schinder and Jacqui Doherty.

Professional songwriter/singer/keyboard/guitar/producer/world citizen Nick Schinder, aka The Child (his long term project and alter ego: www.thechildmusic.co.uk) has won several contests around the world, travelled and gigged around Latin America and Europe, and released 4 albums with The Child, plus, he contributed to countless projects with his playing and songs.

Lyricist Jacqueline Doherty, aka Claudia Flaxton. Jacqueline is a published Poet with the International Society of Poets & Photographer, Diploma 04. After a number of years writing screenplays and poetry for fun, she decided to take her poems and turn them into songs. She set to work with artists that could add melody to her words, Nick being the one with whom she has worked the most, up to the point where they can now call themselves a creative duo. All songs written by Nick Schinder (music) and Jacqui Doherty (lyrics), except “Elephant & Castle” (lyrics & music by Nick Schinder)

Nick & Jacqui agree that the name Deep River Running, ''reflects well our attitude & style of music.''
Personnel: Nick Schinder: Vocals, keyboards & guitars. Jacqui Doherty: Lyrics

Devin Messina Creative minds can’t be bottled in and they must wander freely through, soaking up as much as they can. Devin Messina is no exception. Born in Maryland, Devin’s broad upbringing has allowed her to witness the good and the bad of the Washington, DC metropolitan area. Music was her therapy, and despite her circumstances, she used melody to get through whatever was in her way. Devin first knew that she wanted to perform when she was only 10 years old. Locking the door, and performing in her room, she wrote her first song when she was 12. These early writings were reminiscent of the things that she’d been going through as a youngster. Devin’s drive was apparent very early on. She was able to record in a studio by the age of 12 with her first group, Girl’s In Full Effect (G.I.F.E.). While singing in talent shows in and around DC, Devin also sang in her school choirs and had the opportunity to sing the National Anthem for basketball games. While attending Fort Washington’s Friendly High School, Devin formed a group named “Elation”. After high school, the group started working on an album with producers K.C and Rich Harris. The group would spend days in the studio until they had their songs perfect. Over time the group would experience great creative differences, freeing Devin to pursue her dreams of being a solo artist. Despite her humble beginnings, Devin has been able to make a name for herself in the entertainment industry. She’s worked with very talented producers, like Rich Harris, Lex-D of Bloq Rockaz Production, and Mac Ming. She’s also opened up for artist like Beanie Man, A.Z., Chuck Brown, Marcus Johnson and Trey Songz. She’s also sang the National Anthem at a National Basketball Association Indiana Pacers game. In addition, her talent has given her a chance to perform at very prestigious venues, like the Lincoln Theater, Warner Theater, and Blues Alley. Inspired by Jimmy Hendrix, Bootsy Collins, Betty Davis, Smokey Robinson, Sam Cook, Aretha Franklin, Donnie Hathaway, Michael Jackson, The Beatles and Led Zeppelin, Devin consults a vast library of musical geniuses. Her style is a perfect blend of funk, soul, rock, and pop, and she strives to create music that is similar to nothing else that’s currently being done. A true artist in every sense of the word, Devin spends her spare time perfecting her other creative talents. She enjoys creating abstract drawings, writing, and cosmetology. She is passionate about everything that she touches and works on. Devin hopes to pursue a career in acting in theater and on screen. She also would love to start a clothing line, which would display some of her abstract drawings. From homelessness, to death, to broken hearts, to love pains, Devin’s life is filled with experiences that her listeners can relate to. She has a story to tell, and she hopes that people can learn from the things that she’s experience through her passionate music. “The negative life experiences that you go through shouldn’t dictate your future,” Devin proclaims, “everything happens for a reason, so just live life and learn from it all.” We hope that the world will soon be able to learn through Ms. Devin Messina.

In addition, her talent has given her a chance to perform at very prestigious venues, like the Lincoln Theater, Warner Theater, and Blues Alley. Inspired by Jimmy Hendrix, Bootsy Collins, Betty Davis, Smokey Robinson, Sam Cook, Aretha Franklin, Donnie Hathaway, Michael Jackson, The Beatles and Led Zeppelin, Devin consults a vast library of musical geniuses. Her style is a perfect blend of funk, soul, rock, and pop, and she strives to create music that is similar to nothing else that’s currently being done. A true artist in every sense of the word, Devin spends her spare time perfecting her other creative talents. She enjoys creating abstract drawings, writing, and cosmetology. She is passionate about everything that she touches and works on. Devin hopes to pursue a career in acting in theater and on screen. She also would love to start a clothing line, which would display some of her abstract drawings. From homelessness, to death, to broken hearts, to love pains, Devin’s life is filled with experiences that her listeners can relate to. She has a story to tell, and she hopes that people can learn from the things that she’s experience through her passionate music. “The negative life experiences that you go through shouldn’t dictate your future,” Devin proclaims, “everything happens for a reason, so just live life and learn from it all.” We hope that the world will soon be able to learn through Ms. Devin Messina.

Do you like progressive rock / melodic metal, with funky grooves, with some ethnic /folklore elements??? Then you will like
http://www.stevemisikco.com
The band Steve Misik & Co. is generally of a harder character, but it does not limit itself when it comes to the genre.
The band consists of musicians who have been performing on the Slovak and foreign (Spanish, American, English, Dutch, German, Czech, Hungarian, etc.) music scene. They have previously worked together in various bands and music projects, but the current set “Steve Misik & Co.” settled in April 2013 during the recording of the songs for the debut album “Schizoemphatic” and creating the promo video for the cover version of Deep Purple's ¨You Keep On Moving¨.

The way in which we got to the recording of the debut album was very long and difficult. The first single because of the web administrator's mistake was promoted with incorrect band name “Clone co.”, because he entered the name of the single instead the name of the band, so we kicked his ass.

When the band worked on new songs for the debut album faced with the biggest misfortune, with the health problems of the lead guitarist and co-founder of the band and especially a good friend. Steve Tóth had to be hospitalized. Steve Misik had to play abroad as a session musician in different projects, because of the break and money required for recording and so on. That time Steve Tóth suddenly passed away, which painfully affected everybody, because of his creative benefit, friendship and enormous love for music (when he found out that he will not be able to play guitar after his heart surgery, he fell into a coma and doctors failed to wake him). Steve Misik composed and arranged the song "My waves" based on his riff and lyrics, they worked together on that song before his death. The album Schizoemphatic is dedicated to his memory.
The band doesn't like to label its genre. We grew up listening hard rock, metal bands but we've been influenced by funk, soul, blues, classical music or jazz. Our music is based on the concept of trying different genres, different imaginary worlds, different fantasies in every song but keeping our own face. In the lyrics we point out the civilization problems of the society and mental world of the human being. That's how we define our music direction in the media interviews.

Eric Whited
Composer/Producer
WhitedOut@Gmail.com
440-221-4870

Classically trained on piano from the ages of 8-16 all the while white-knuckling performances in competitions at The Cleveland Music Settlement and The University of Akron. At age 11, in the Summer of 1978, I was a member of the Cleveland Orchestra Boy's Choir performing Carl Orff's "Carmina Burana" at Blossom Music and am hopeful this isn’t my only 15 minutes of fame in life. Got my first electric guitar from a garage sale at age 16 and taught myself how to play Stairway to Heaven since it just didn't sound right on piano.

After completing two years at Thee Ohio State University's School of Music, decided to move to Hollywood, California in July of 1989 and graduated from Musician's Institute/Guitar Institute of Technology - actually quite an accomplishment considering the vast majority didn't. Was signed to Rag Records with my band, The Mustard Seeds and as a producer for the band, Treehouse Toys for Planet Earth Records. While on Planet Earth, played at the first anniversary of 9/11 for a benefit promoted by KROQ. Even licensed Music to Playboy Entertainment for their cable channel that gave me a certain infamous reputation around town. Took my first stab at composing to film when I composed Title and Credit Cues for the Independent Film, "Man's Best Friend" (Maxwell Productions). Signed a Development Deal with the Entertainment Law Firm, Madison Law Group (my first dealing with entertainment lawyers) and produced a ballad for recording artist, Satori. Signed a Development Deal with Cornerstone Studios (Fleetwood Mac, Motley Crue) to produce vocalist, Tami Johnson. Went back to school at UCLA Extension School's Film Scoring Certificate Program and composed for Chamber Orchestras, Small Ensembles, Quintets, Quartets, and Trios that I do consider my greatest educational experience to date.

In May of 2003, I moved back to The FarEast Side of Cleveland, Ohio because of a family tragedy and created WhitedOut Productions & Studio on Murray Hill producing seven Cds for commercial release including Jim Miller’s double CD, In-Trance-It: an absolute thrill since I have been following him since Oroboros. Considering the fact that my recording studio was in an art gallery building, performed live at Murray Hill Art Walks, SPARX Gallery Hops, and Fashion Shows. Performed with vocalist, Susan Fletcher at The Abbey Road on the River Festival in Louisville, KY and Louise Harrison, George's sister, complimented us for our version of "Imagine". Got back into Film/Television composing and contributed music to the Cleveland-based television series, "Out of Darkness" including the Main Theme (see YouTube interview above). Then went on to produce the Cd entitled, "HARP ROCK" for Harpist, Christina Kline performing 14 Classic Rock standards that never sound so serene. Also produced Christina's harp version of ZZ Top’s, “Gimme All Your Lovin’ ” for the FOX Television show, “BONES” and learned a lot about The Industry through dealings with Fox's Music division. Was thrilled when Northern Ohio Live Magazine’s television show, “Live from the Circle” used my song, "Cool Jazz for Ma'" for their main theme for a 13 week run on PBS. Played solo two years in a row at the Let's Get Together Festival in a natural amphitheater in Central, PA and have decided playing at outdoor music festivals is the way to go.

Then in 2012, moved back to HollyWeird and out there, I am know as a "he played a mean guitar" and formed my first cover band, The WizGuys. Got to jam a Zep medley of Whole Lotta Love/The Lemon Song/Bring On Home in the old clubs I used to play in with The Mustard Seeds - a total kick. But, there is a reason why Axl wrote, "Welcome To The Jungle" and I got the hell outta Dodge.

Returned back to the Cleveland area in 2014 and became the keyboardist at Unity Center of the Heights which not only enhanced my performance skills, but my Spiritual skills as well. Formed a cover band that we play the first part of a cover, then jam on it for an undetermined amount of time. And now I am concentrating on my Cool Jazz & R&B music plus a new cover band with electric rock harpist Kristy Kline entitled - Into The Light: A Pink Floyd Experience that Kristy sings and plays harp to!

extra:
Craymo BIO

Craymo was born Craig Stephen Raymo in Massena, New York and grew up in nearby Ogdensburg, a quiet little city on the St. Lawrence River bordering Canada. Music seemed to possess his soul from an early age as he had always tried to imitate the singers and bands eminating from his little 45 rpm record player. In 3rd grade he picked up the alto saxophone taking lessons from Kenneth Van Winkle, father of future Grammy winner Dixon Van Winkle. Craymo continued taking lessons and played in elementary and Jr. and Sr.High Bands and the school Jazz Rock group. Craig wrote his first song when he was 16. He sang in the school choir from elementary through high school. The young performer craved the stage and graced it every chance he got joining the local vaudeville style minstrel group Showtime. Craymo performed in community theatre and high school drama and musical theatre productions.
As a senior in high school he took interest in DJing and got a job spinning at Big Ed's Dallas Lounge and also at a local radio station where co-workers first started calling him Craymo. Craymo went to Fredonia State University majoring in Broadcasting with a minor in drama.

Feeling the call of the big city, Craig left college and moved to Los Angeles to pursue his dreams. He soon landed acting gigs in the TV soap operas General Hospital and days Of Our livess, most recently in the HBO original film Recount. Craymo continued to DJ in Nightclubs and was one of the first "video jocks" to beat mix videos! All the while focused on his music Craymo wrote hundreds of songs and started recording demos in Los Angeles recording studios. He auditioned to be the lead singer for several bands but ultimately realized his destiny was to be a solo artist. The determined young man took vocal lessons with R&B great Bobby Womack and recorded a demo of one of his songs. Craymo then met record producer David Longoria who took him under his wing and they recorded his first professionally recorded song Love Touch and filmed his first music video. Then they went on to create several more songs including Craymo's first EP entitled Be My Girl who's title track was licensed in the indie film Paper Thin Immortals. The next video was Take It Slow with a sixties beatnick vibe and the song was licensed in the indie film Accidents Don't Happen. Craymo appeared as a male vocalist on Star Search 89 with Ed McMahan. He formed several backup bands performing at the Whiskey A Go Go, The Roxy, Genghis Cohen and opened up shows for Smashmouth, The Plimsouls and Fishbone. He then met record producer Chris Irwin and recorded several songs in his Malibu studio. Craymo then ran into his old friend, songwriter and producer Brandon Jarrett. They went into the studio and magic happened. Combining their song catalogs into one company, Moho Productions, LLC. They recorded One Love One World which became a worldwide phenomenon being featured on the United Nations project UNESCO web site www.newsongsforpeace.org. School teachers all over the world downloaded the song, taught it to their students who then performed it at their schools in the USA, Canada, China and Australia!

Craymo has been a semi-finalist and finalist in several songwriting competitions including the 2014 Hollywood Music In Media Awards, 2014 Right Out TV Awards, 2014 Indie Music Channel Awards, 2014 Independent Music Network Awards (Winner New Discovery Artist), 2014 UK Songwriting Competition and the 2012 Australian Music Oz Awards. His songs have been licensed in the indie films, Culture Shock, Gabe The Cupid Dog, Super Southern Sweet Sixteen, Silly Movie 2 and Successful Failures 2. Also in television including The Mysteries Of Laura, The X Games
( ESPN), Dance Mom's (TLC), The Orlando Citrus Parade, Sinbad's Reality U (pilot), Toddlers and Tiaras (TLC) and Chris and John To The Rescue (Canada). His first full lenght CD Cosmos and followup Cosmos (Singles and Remixes) are available on iTunes. Craymo is currently receiving airplay on commercial and internet radio all over the world.
His influences include Duran Duran, George Michael, The Beatles, Morrissey, Michael Jackson, Cyndi Lauper, David Bowie, Elton John, Sting and The Cars.

"I started recording a few 'covers' for a bit of fun in 2005. Then when Hurricane Katrina hit, many My Space fans answered my call when I created the Paul Caroul Challenge: a pledge to follow my lead and give half of what you own to help the victims get back on their feet. So many wonderful people donated stuff that I could give to the right places to expedite the process. I later located one gal who came to CA with her car and the shirt off her back after losing everything- and around the country Madison Paige fans sent gift cards, goods, etc. and together we were able to help furnish her new dwellings. Everyone who would gave half, I pledged that I would record a specialty CD for and it is now done exclusively for them and a few of my friends. It took just under two years in between my Madison Paige recordings. My heart was warmed by others' generosity to help, and so the project truly became a Labor Of Love. " Quote: -Paul Caroul February 2007

title: The Big Bag Blues
extra: I spent my time playing every place I could on the West Coast. From small restaurants to 130,000 people concerts. One of these concerts was Satsup Tin Cup Races in Olympia, Washington, then we came down and played Portland, Oregon, San Fransisco, California and then ended up in Hollywood in early 1971. I was the founder of the Johnathan Davis Group. I wrote all the songs and was the lead singer. I played in Hollywood in the 70's, was on KTTV, The Elliot Mence show, I played on KPFK Live after 12:00, I did a Griffith Park concert with El Chicano and played many living room concerts for the rich and famous I also played The Trubador and Filthy McNasty's. The Johnathan Davis Group was the only group ever to play live on KMET at that time. Recorded at Fat chance, Columbia Studio D and at their showcase, also recorded at Paramount Studios, where i met Frank Zappa and his family, Played these clubs outside The L.A. area, Finicans Rainbow, The In Crowd ,The Golden Bear are just a few of the clubs I played in. I have been on the same shows with Steve Miller Band, The Youngbloods, Bad Company, Big Foot, Little Feet, El Chicano, Ike and Tina Turner, Paul Revere and the Raiders, Linda Ronstadt, Flash Cadillac and the Continental Kids, John Hammond, Country Joe and the Fish and many more that I can't recall. Gene Borges had my back- he was the owner of Sunset Transit Classic Cars down by The Hyatt House and he showed me the best of Hollywood. My best friend was Michael Todd, Elizabeth Taylors son. Mike was delivering gold for Howard Hughes. Mike introduced me to him and we were the ones who took Liz's fragrance White Diamonds to the manufacturer. I ended up selling a Rolls Royce to Wilt Chamberlain and I met Ricky Nelson and his two sons there on the car lot. I burned a fat one with Buddy Miles. It was the early '70's, what can I say, ya know? I met Cindy Lauper, we hung out for a day. I also met David Bowie. Thanks goes out all my fans old and new :)

title: Pop / Easy Listening / Soundtrack
extra:
Hello,I don't really consider myself an artist/performer instead just simply a musician/songwriter.Some of my influences include the beatles,the eagles,billy joel,bob dylan.I'm not looking to be famous at all but if my tunes get some major attention that would be very cool.I'
m most interested in getting my songs pitched to/cut by other artists and also music licensing deal of any kind i'm open to anything/anywhere,tv,movies,tv ads etc.I've had some minor licensing deals in the past few years but not the 'big' one yet.I have a mix of songs available in country,adult pop,adult contemporary,i have a reggae tune,a ukulele song,a blues song even a quirky fun playful wedding anthem/song i think you'll like.you can find more of my stuff at vibedeck.com/ljwarren and soundclick.com/ljwarren.anyway hope you find something of mine that interests you.thanks so much for your valuable time and thanks for listening.lj

title: Balcony Of Wonder
extra:
Alexandra Legouix and The Sunflowers! have created a sophisticated but accessible fusion of latin, jazz, soul, reggae and pop influences. We make music that people can relate to on many different levels... think about it... chill to it... dance to it... make love to it... funky, modern, relevant lyrics and tunes, set to a backing skilfully provided by vastly experienced musicians. See http://www.alexandralegouix.biz/ for more info and details.

Winning BBC Introducing in January 2010 has helped launch Alexandra into the limelight and provided her with new and exciting opportunities. In April, Alexandra and her newly formed band (The Sunflowers!) played the BBC Introducing gig in reading with much success - landing new gigs as a result and developing a bigger and more loyal fanbase. As a result, AL & The Sunflowers have been asked to go in to the BBC Berkshire radio station for an interview and two tracks! They have also been invited to perform on the main stage at the Inside:Outside Festival in Reading on Saturday 7th August! As well as support from the BBC, they have received much press attention and recently have had featured articles in local and national newspapers.

extra:
Elvis has been passionate about music for all of his adult life, funneling his
creativity through his singing, songwriting, and music-making skills. His latest CD,
Life, is his 8th LP recording in a long, illustrious continuing career. This Georgia
native, born in Atlanta and raised in the small town of Palmetto, Georgia, still
currently resides in his hometown. At the young age of 16, Elvis joined the United States
army and at 17 years old was sent off to Lie Kie, Vietnam, where he spent more than a
year fighting for his country with the First Infantry Division his lasst year in the army
was spent in Aberdeen, MD. This patriotic multi-talented artist has been compared to
Merle Haggard, and has been recognized significantly for his poems and songwriting. Aside
from making music, his other hobbies include hunting, fishing, and eating. Elvis has a
sweet tooth for ice cream, cake, and all kinds of fruit, from cherries to watermelons!
But you best believe he’ll grill up a mean Boston Butt in a heart beat! Off the grill,
Elvis has cooked up the design for the world renowned Guitar House in Fayetteville,
Georgia. Elvis, the sole designer and builder of the landmark, spent 16 years creating
this spectacular, guitar-shaped home. Pictures and videos of Georgia’s TV Channel 5 News
coverage can be seen on www.YouTube.com and throughout the world wide web. Elvis is a
member of BMI, CMA, ICMA, VVA, VVMF, VF, American Legion, etc., and owns Guitar House
Records Inc. (won “Label of the Year” in 1990. Elvis’ first recordings, “Vietnam Blues”
and “Loving a Soldier”, originally recorded in 1967, won Patriotic Song of the Year in
1990. In 2005, Elvis won the COMA International Male Recording Artist of the Year. 2007
was the year Elvis received the prestigious accolade as International Poet of the Year
for “Loving a Soldier”. Elvis created the music video honoring the 25th anniversary of
the Vietnam Veterans Wall in 2007, and made music and poetry for the Vietnam Veterans
Fund with his “Life of Elvis Lloyd Carden”. Prior to his new CD “LIFE”, Elvis L. Carden
released the single, “American Rebel”, which is currently on distribution through HMG
Nashville earning music reviews from NY, NY & Ehking, TX, Find it here. To learn more
about Elvis, or to download songs and buy Elvis’ CDs and goods on the internet at:

extra:
'''Jeankarl Lattán''' (Caracas, Venezuela), conocido artísticamente como '''Jeankarl''', es un cantante, productor, diseñador gráfico, director y compositor. Fundador de la empresa [[Jeankarl Records]] Conocido por su producción musical «El poder del Reggaeton», «Cultura Reggaeton» y radiado temas musicales como «Me baila lento», «La veo en la disco», «Tu y yo» y recientemente «La Playa» bajo su propio sello Jeankarl Records.

== Biografía ==

Jeankarl nace en Caracas, destacado por su habilidad en el dominio y versatilidad de diferentes especialidades y profesiones, se graduó como técnico medio en Administración y procesamiento de datos, posteriormente inicio sus estudios de ingeniería mención informática, adquiriendo a su vez por su cuenta conocimientos relacionados al mundo artístico (tecnología, marketing, música, diseño y audiovisual).

En el año 2006 se convierte en el fundador de la empresa Producciones Jeankarl Records C.A., productora musical especializada en el producción de nuevos artistas musicales del género urbano en donde desarrolla sus conocimientos para convertirse en el CEO (Chief Executive Officer – Director Ejecutivo) de su propia empresa en estado de compañía startup (compañía de arranque). Conocido en el mundo musical urbano como “El que todo lo hace” por iniciar su carrera artística haciendo todo lo relacionado a la música por sí solo, convirtiéndose en su propio productor musical, cantautor, compositor, diseñador gráfico, director, promotor y manejador. Posteriormente en el año 2008 gana el concurso "Lánzate a la fama" realizado por la empresa Pepsi donde se le otorga el primer lugar por ser el artista de mayor apoyo web.
En el transcurrir de los años se convirtió en el productor de diferentes talentos bajo el nombre de DJ Yan “El de las melodías por segundo”, así como también hace su propio lanzamiento como artista de reggaetón.

Actualmente Jeankarl Records ha pasado de ser una empresa productora de música a una empresa Spin-off (empresas derivadas), especializada en diferentes ramas como Diseño Gráfico, Audiovisual y Música, así como alianzas con diferentes empresas que ofrecen dichos servicios.

Entre los acontecimientos que destacan a dicho artista, este fue el creador de la primera página web de reggaeton del mundo publicada en Internet en 1998 con el nombre de reggaetonoficial donde se mostraban imágenes de los artistas del género, música, letras, historias, noticias entre otras. Dicha página web sirvió como base de información para el lanzamiento de otras web.
Jeankarl se encuentra trabajando actualemtne como productor de talentos asi como haciendo nuevas producciones musicales de genero urbano.

== Carrera musical ==
=== 2006—2010: inicio musical ===
En el 2006 es lanzada como experimento de producion bajo sus propios medios el album "El poder del reggaeton" donde Jeankarl desarrolla todo lo necesario para hacer un lanzamiento oficial asi como el proyecto de empresa Jeankarl Records.

En el Año 2008 es lanzado el tema “Ella volvió” siendo uno de los primeros sencillos de Jeankarl lanzado de su producción por internet en el año 2008 en uno de los momentos auges del reggaetón siendo una buena partida para entrar en el mundo del genero urbano.

===2009—presente: Disco debut y éxito radial ===
Posteriormente hizo el lanzamiento del tema “La veo en la disco” en el 2009 en conjunto con una producción mejorada titulada Cultura Reggaeton y su primer video musical en alta calidad para el 2010 hizo que curiosamente se compartiera a través de las redes sociales de mayor auge del momento.

Parte de su exito se baso en que no era secreto para nadie que él mismo se encargaba de hacer la promoción de su música tanto vía internet como en los locales más sonados de Caracas, utilizando sus estrategias de Marketing logrando incluso sonar canciones a nivel internacional como lo fue un tema controversial llamado “Me baila lento” por tratarse de un remix de featuring inédito.

No bastaba solamente con que fuera él mismo el que promocionara su música sin ayuda de disqueras o terceros sino que también el mismo se hacia la música, las grabaciones, los arreglos, las letras, la página web, los diseños, los videos y todo lo que tuviera que ver con su carrera musical bajo el nombre de su compañía llamada Jeankarl Records, de allí parte el nombre de “El que todo lo hace”.

Posteriormente su trabajo como productor musical se exparse y es reconocido bajo el nombre de DJ Yan debido a la llamada de atención de su música entre los seguidores del genero urbano incluyendo a los nuevos talentos que buscaron apoyo en su compañía para que al igual que él pudieran realizar sus producciones musicales por lo que en el 2011 Jeankarl lanza su producción como productor musical titulado DJ Yan “El de las melodías por segundo” donde se pueden escuchar una gama de nuevos talentos producidos por Jeankarl.

No es sino para el 2012 en donde decide lanzar otro sencillo musical titulado “La Playa” que en conjunto es lanzado con un video musical en alta calidad para la producción “La Reunión” donde se hace hincapié sobre los mejores productores de música urbana en Venezuela, así como temas remixes inéditos de lo más sonado del momento.

En el año 2013 escuchamos algunos temas remixes inéditos así como estuvo dedicado trabajando como productor y director de su empresa Jeankarl Records y lo que hizo que para el 2014 hiciera el lanzamiento de dos nuevos videos musicales de su canción “Traición” y “Tu y Yo”, en conjunto con la evolución de la compañía Jeankarl Records con cambio de imagen y nuevas ramas de producción y desde el 2015 trabajando en nuevas producciones musicales el cual han sido lanzadas a través de las diferentes plataformas digitales.

extra:
Hope is a Singer/Songwriter/Music Producer from North Carolina.
Her genre's include Pop, Contemporary Country, Rock, Hip-Hop, Adult Contemporary,
and R&B. Hope writes with other Songwriters, Music Producers, and Artists from
the US and all over the World. Hope writes from the heart with lyrics that seem
to get you hooked right from the start with great melodies, combined with memorable
hooks. Her music can best be described as "story telling" and can make you feel like
you've "been there and done that". Hope's writing goals are to be the major songwriting
force behind all the mainstream music that you hear today on the Radio, in Film, and on TV.
Hope is devoted to giving all she's got to her professional songwriting and continues to
grow musically and emotionally with each new song she creates.

To listen to more songs from Hope that were collaborations
and solo projects, please visit www.broadjam.com/hope

extra: I spent my time playing every place I could on the West Coast. From small restaurants to 130,000 people concerts. One of these concerts was Satsup Tin Cup Races in Olympia, Washington, then we came down and played Portland, Oregon, San Fransisco, California and then ended up in Hollywood in early 1971. I was the founder of the Johnathan Davis Group. I wrote all the songs and was the lead singer. I played in Hollywood in the 70's, was on KTTV, The Elliot Mence show, I played on KPFK Live after 12:00, I did a Griffith Park concert with El Chicano and played many living room concerts for the rich and famous I also played The Trubador and Filthy McNasty's. The Johnathan Davis Group was the only group ever to play live on KMET at that time. Recorded at Fat chance, Columbia Studio D and at their showcase, also recorded at Paramount Studios, where i met Frank Zappa and his family, Played these clubs outside The L.A. area, Finicans Rainbow, The In Crowd ,The Golden Bear are just a few of the clubs I played in. I have been on the same shows with Steve Miller Band, The Youngbloods, Bad Company, Big Foot, Little Feet, El Chicano, Ike and Tina Turner, Paul Revere and the Raiders, Linda Ronstadt, Flash Cadillac and the Continental Kids, John Hammond, Country Joe and the Fish and many more that I can't recall. Gene Borges had my back- he was the owner of Sunset Transit Classic Cars down by The Hyatt House and he showed me the best of Hollywood. My best friend was Michael Todd, Elizabeth Taylors son. Mike was delivering gold for Howard Hughes. Mike introduced me to him and we were the ones who took Liz's fragrance White Diamonds to the manufacturer. I ended up selling a Rolls Royce to Wilt Chamberlain and I met Ricky Nelson and his two sons there on the car lot. I burned a fat one with Buddy Miles. It was the early '70's, what can I say, ya know? I met Cindy Lauper, we hung out for a day. I also met David Bowie. Thanks goes out all my fans old and new :)

title: Because you Live
extra:
Courtney Larmond has grown up playing guitar from a young age because seeing and hearing his dad play his banjo switched on a light inside of him and his love for music was born and began to develop from there. Having 4 singing sisters and Banjo playing dad, music was a major influence in the home growing up.
He has always enjoyed playing along with his dad at home. When his father would rehearse, Courtney would have his plastic guitar that his dad bought him and from there he started to watch people playing, began school music lessons and eventually took everything and built a style of his own, along the way learning to play the Bass Guitar, Keyboards and Drum. Gaining experience whilst playing in Church led to Courtney playing in session forums and progressing to working in the studio applying his skills to production and writing.

He has been a musician for the best part of 25 years, gaining respect as a guitarist and building a good reputation playing guitar on the gospel circuit. Courtney has played on many projects and live performances.

He has been privileged to work with a lot of musicians, soloists and choirs over the years. The likes of
London Community Gospel Choir,
Noel Robinson,
Visual Ministry Choir,
Kingdom Choir,
Marvin Sapp (USA),
Vicky Winans (USA),
Jennifer Philips,
The Wade Bro's and
Ian Green
Trinity girls school Christmas show
New Testament church, school of music teaching guitar.
Italy Gospel music festival
New Years Eve music festival Scotland
to name a few.

As a writer and producer Courtney is always keen to support young talent and features them on tracks to help them develop and grow. Working with the youth a lot, he has seen the ability and determination that is out there so he wants to at least offer a helping hand to open the door for them.
He has worked hard to achieve what he has already produced in the music field and continues to spread the knowledge and experiences he has obtained over the years.

Barbara Lee George is a singer/songwriter whose voice and compositions appeal to a broad audience; from Jazz, Latin, Folk, Rock, Country, Hip Hop, Symphonic to Lullaby. Barbara and her band will take you for a heart-felt and mind expanding ride that will leave you better for having made the journey.
Saddle-up and enjoy the ride!!!

July 2010, Barbara Lee George and Even Steven Levee, her bassist and musical producer completed their latest CD project "Protected By Love". This CD is simply a work of art - from its completely original 10 tracks of hit, after hit (in every genre) to its stunning original cover art, contributed by the internationally renowned contemporary cubistic artist, Yuroz. Barbara's taste in art is unquestionable and it is apparent that her lifetime’s exposure to brilliant musicianship guided her in forming this group. Barbara's Band is a musical tour de force that begs to be heard live!

extra:
Yenisley is a regional touring pop/rock, female vocalist, backed by a 5 piece band. Born in Havana, Cuba, this bi-lingual singer/songwriter has been creating a buzz for sometime now. While maintaining her spanish roots, Yenisley embraces the american dream. She uses her marketable image, dynamic vocal range, and extraordinary stage presence, to captivate audiences of all ages. Yenisley has blended her pop, rock, and punk influences, to create her own original sound consisting of powerful hooks and catchy melodies. Her stage show is full of energy. She has a unique blend of original material, as well as cover songs from some of today's biggest artists. Her band consists of young and energetic musicians, who know how to work a crowd. They combine skill, determination and fun, while creating a passion on stage that leaves a lasting impression with the audience. Big things are in store for Yenisley. Her drive is recognized by her fans and they truly appreciate her loyalty and commitment. Having already planted herself within the southeast region, she is looking to make bigger moves by crossing over to a national audience. Her intent is to captivate a million fans the same way she captivated her first fan. Some of Yenisley's notable performances are as follows:

- Opening act for Collective Soul at WMMO 98.9/Gibson Concert Series (Orlando, FL)
- Showcase artist at Florida Music Festival (Orlando, FL)
- Showcase artist at Miami Music Festival (Miami, FL)
- Orange Ave Jam (Orlando, FL)
- Pumpkin Festival (Sarasota, FL)
- Feature artist at 98.9 FM's Rockin' Lake Eola (Orlando, FL)
- Englewood Music Festival Main Stage (Englewood, FL)
- Charleston, SC 4th of July Show (main stage)
- Yenisley has performed at some of the top venues including, but not limited to:

Blue Martini - (Miami, Orlando, West Palm Beach, Boca Raton, Ft. Lauderdale)
Ocean's 10 - Miami Beach
Mansion - Miami Beach
Van Dyke - Miami Beach
The Social - Orlando
Porterhouse - Boca Raton
Mango's - Ft. Lauderdale

title: The Truth
extra:
Yenisley is a regional touring pop/rock, female vocalist, backed by a 5 piece band. Born in Havana, Cuba, this bi-lingual singer/songwriter has been creating a buzz for sometime now. While maintaining her spanish roots, Yenisley embraces the american dream. She uses her marketable image, dynamic vocal range, and extraordinary stage presence, to captivate audiences of all ages. Yenisley has blended her pop, rock, and punk influences, to create her own original sound consisting of powerful hooks and catchy melodies. Her stage show is full of energy. She has a unique blend of original material, as well as cover songs from some of today's biggest artists. Her band consists of young and energetic musicians, who know how to work a crowd. They combine skill, determination and fun, while creating a passion on stage that leaves a lasting impression with the audience. Big things are in store for Yenisley. Her drive is recognized by her fans and they truly appreciate her loyalty and commitment. extra:
Elvis has been passionate about music for all of his adult life, funneling his
creativity through his singing, songwriting, and music-making skills. His latest CD,
Life, is his 8th LP recording in a long, illustrious continuing career. This Georgia
native, born in Atlanta and raised in the small town of Palmetto, Georgia, still
currently resides in his hometown. At the young age of 16, Elvis joined the United States
army and at 17 years old was sent off to Lie Kie, Vietnam, where he spent more than a
year fighting for his country with the First Infantry Division his lasst year in the army
was spent in Aberdeen, MD. This patriotic multi-talented artist has been compared to
Merle Haggard, and has been recognized significantly for his poems and songwriting. Aside
from making music, his other hobbies include hunting, fishing, and eating. Elvis has a
sweet tooth for ice cream, cake, and all kinds of fruit, from cherries to watermelons!
But you best believe he’ll grill up a mean Boston Butt in a heart beat! Off the grill,
Elvis has cooked up the design for the world renowned Guitar House in Fayetteville,
Georgia. Elvis, the sole designer and builder of the landmark, spent 16 years creating
this spectacular, guitar-shaped home. Pictures and videos of Georgia’s TV Channel 5 News
coverage can be seen on www.YouTube.com and throughout the world wide web. Elvis is a
member of BMI, CMA, ICMA, VVA, VVMF, VF, American Legion, etc., and owns Guitar House
Records Inc. (won “Label of the Year” in 1990. Elvis’ first recordings, “Vietnam Blues”
and “Loving a Soldier”, originally recorded in 1967, won Patriotic Song of the Year in
1990. In 2005, Elvis won the COMA International Male Recording Artist of the Year. 2007
was the year Elvis received the prestigious accolade as International Poet of the Year
for “Loving a Soldier”. Elvis created the music video honoring the 25th anniversary of
the Vietnam Veterans Wall in 2007, and made music and poetry for the Vietnam Veterans
Fund with his “Life of Elvis Lloyd Carden”. Prior to his new CD “LIFE”, Elvis L. Carden
released the single, “American Rebel”, which is currently on distribution through HMG
Nashville earning music reviews from NY, NY & Ehking, TX, Find it here. To learn more
about Elvis, or to download songs and buy Elvis’ CDs and goods on the internet at:

extra: "RYAN MORENO is a singer / songwriter with an innovative guitar style and insightful lyrics. Born in Chicago, and raised on Robert Johnson, Johnny Cash and Stevie Ray Vaughn, RYAN MORENO displays a songwriting maturity that is older than his years. RYAN has honed his acoustic guitar and piano playing to a sharp edge that drives his lyrics and moves his audience. RYAN's music has evolved into progressive pop-blues-rock with a touch of style from John Mayer. RYAN's lyrics tell stories people relate to, as he sings of heart moving inklings of love, personal loss, and the greater human condition that is so much a part of his innate understanding of the blues. His own life has not been simple, but his optimism comes through in his up beat numbers that lift the soul. (Stephen Kastner- Door County Peninsula Pulse 2007) .. .. "— Stephn Kastner, Door County Peninsula Pulse

title: Nobody Somewhere
extra:
ALL DAY SUCKER

Morty Coyle (Vocals), AKA Celebrity DJ ‘DJ Morty And Jordan Summers (Keys) Found
Early Success, Two Major Label Deals And Won “Best Pop Song” and “Best Song” In The U.S.A. Songwriting Competition. They Have Licensed Tracks To ABC’s “Happy Endings”, CBS’ “Swingtown”, MTV’s“Laguna Beach”, “The Hills”, “The Real World", “Road Rules” and “Breaking Bonaduce”

         
Former Maroon 5 drummer Ryan Dusick is a huge fan: “All Day Sucker plays soulful pop music, classic grooves with a velvety voice singing cleverly ironic lyrics. I’ve seen them play about fifty times and I still want more!” Actor/comedian Andy Dick is also on board: “All Day Sucker’s ‘Worst Case Scenario’ makes me wanna shake my ass.” And Kelly Osbourne says, “I f***ing love them!”
           
Following up their Self Titled debut album produced by Evan Frankfort (Wallflowers, Pete Yorn) and Warren Huart (The Fray, Aerosmith) is The Big Pretend. Part adoring valentine, part cleverly biting commentary on their hometown, All Day Sucker’s new album is a full length bona fide concept album written by Coyle and Summers that shows their pride in L.A. even as it pokes fun at the occasional ridiculousness and idiosyncrasies of a city where everyone has some connection to the film industry. Produced by Noah Shain (Orson, As Tall As Lions, Dead Sarah) and released on the duo’s label Trademark Entertainment/big WOW music, the set is an inspired twist on the sounds of the classic rock era reinvented for modern ears.

You can watch their video for “The Picture (That Took Me)” at by clicking here.

extra:
Rick Ivanoff was born in Toronto, Canada on February 9, 1956. He is a published Canadian songwriter who writes catchy hooks and melodies in the styles of Pop, Easy Listening, Country, Folk and Rock. He has performed live on Breakfast Television in Toronto, Global News at Noon across Canada, as well as in music videos shown on CMT.

Rick’s songs have been recorded by different artists and used in television shows and film. His influences include such great harmony bands as The Byrds, The Eagles, Blue Rodeo, Poco, Buffalo Springfield, Firefall, CSNY, Alison Krauss and Union Station, as well as the great artists and songwriters Neil Young, Jackson Browne, Garth Brooks, Dan Fogelberg, Joni Mitchell, Rob Thomas and so many more.

Rick is involved in the music industry as a songwriter,composer, performer, producer, jingle writer, voice over talent, studio musician, publisher, promoter and licensing agent.

ALL DAY SUCKER

Morty Coyle (Vocals), AKA Celebrity DJ ‘DJ Morty And Jordan Summers (Keys) Found
Early Success, Two Major Label Deals And Won “Best Pop Song” and “Best Song” In The U.S.A. Songwriting Competition. They Have Licensed Tracks To ABC’s “Happy Endings”, CBS’ “Swingtown”, MTV’s“Laguna Beach”, “The Hills”, “The Real World", “Road Rules” and “Breaking Bonaduce”


Former Maroon 5 drummer Ryan Dusick is a huge fan: “All Day Sucker plays soulful pop music, classic grooves with a velvety voice singing cleverly ironic lyrics. I’ve seen them play about fifty times and I still want more!” Actor/comedian Andy Dick is also on board: “All Day Sucker’s ‘Worst Case Scenario’ makes me wanna shake my ass.” And Kelly Osbourne says, “I f***ing love them!”

Following up their Self Titled debut album produced by Evan Frankfort (Wallflowers, Pete Yorn) and Warren Huart (The Fray, Aerosmith) is The Big Pretend. Part adoring valentine, part cleverly biting commentary on their hometown, All Day Sucker’s new album is a full length bona fide concept album written by Coyle and Summers that shows their pride in L.A. even as it pokes fun at the occasional ridiculousness and idiosyncrasies of a city where everyone has some connection to the film industry. Produced by Noah Shain (Orson, As Tall As Lions, Dead Sarah) and released on the duo’s label Trademark Entertainment/big WOW music, the set is an inspired twist on the sounds of the classic rock era reinvented for modern ears.

You can watch their video for “The Picture (That Took Me)” at by clicking here.

extra: In the year 2030, Pat Benatar, AC/DC, Aerosmith, and Avril Lavigne, build a supergroup and travel back into the year 2013 in an time machine, to bring some fresh wind into the music scene. Chris Dair was inspired to play the guitar at an early age by Manitas De Plata who triggered a passion for guitar and a love of flamenco guitar. At age 14 he developed a passion for blues and gigged in London at venues like Ronnie Scotts with John Mayall, John McVie and George Melly.

As a young lead guitarist Chris jammed/played with many of the R&B and rock legends of our time, including Rory Gallagher, Jimmy Paige, Ginger Baker, the late Paul Kossof, Captain Beefheart, Dick Stubbs (Juicy Lucy), Linda Lewis (Ferris Wheel), Dave Davies (The Kinks), Roy Wood (Wizard), Mickey Finn (T-Rex), Mark Knopfler, Led Zeppelin, Peter Green, Jeff Beck. Most unforgettably with the great blues legend Bukka White. More recently Noel Redding (Jimi Hendrix Experience) and John Coughlan (Status Quo).
Major influences include Jimi Hendrix, John McLaughlin, and Frank Zappa.

Composer for film/media industry:
Bermuda Cablevision; French Films; Nickelodeon; E!; Romanian General and Broadcasting; Singaporean Films; USA Television and Cable; Guinness World Records (USA); Intimate Portraits (Cable TV USA); The Vibe, Brian Waddell (USA); The Surf Show (USA); True Hollywood Story (USA); Australasia (Apra) Films; ITV; Channel 4; Planet Television; London Weekend TV; Central TV.

Discography: Chris is currently working on a new Blues Album.

Chris began playing guitar at 5 yrs old when he first heard Manitas De Plata, who inspired in him a passion for guitar and a love of flamenco guitar. At age fourteen he developed a passion for blues and went on to gigs in London at venues like Ronnie Scotts with John Mayall, John McVie and George Melly.

As a young lead guitarist he also jammed/played with many of the R&B and rock legends of our time, including Rory Gallagher, Jimmy Paige, Ginger Baker, the late Paul Kossof, Captain Beefheart, Dick Stubbs (Juicy Lucy), Linda Lewis (Ferris Wheel), Dave Davies (The Kinks), Roy Wood (Wizard), Mickey Finn (T-Rex), Mark Knopfler, Led Zeppelin, Peter Green, Jeff Beck. Most unforgettably with the great blues legend Bukka White.

More recently Noel Redding (Jimi Hendrix Experience) and John Coughlan (Status Quo).

Discography:
GUITARRAGA - World Jazz Blues Fusion, released 6 June 2011.
CROSSROADS TO FREEDOM - a dedicated Blues album, a collection of blues from Miississippi Delta to Chicago street, to blues rock.
WHAT CHAINS? is a collection of various genres of music; featuring "Obsession" [blues jazz] and "I Can Live" [rock ballad].
"STRANGE ISLAND" is blues jazz, lyrical, blues rock, latin and more, a concept encouraged by the late Freddie Cousaert. Freddie was a Motown legend and Manager/Producer of Marvin Gayes Sexual Healing, Diana Ross, and Bobby Womac.

extra: Alex Hirsch is a musician/song-writer/producer born in 1966 in New York City. He learned to play the piano at 9 years old, while living in Reseda California. A couple of years later he found weed and the Beatles, and begged his mother for a guitar. 30 years later, Alex is still rockin' daily, collaborating with such notables as Elliot Randall, Ice-T, Too Short, Black Silver, BIONIK, Griffen and several other great talents in several musical genres. Currently he is working on his third solo record titled Tick Tock Clock, due out very soon! He also has several videos up on YOUTUBE, just search for Alex Hirsch and some reference able material will emerge. (We all love you tube). Alex Hirsch is the son of the legendary television and theater actor, Judd Hirsch, who played “Alex Reiger” on the hit show TAXI, which aired on ABC and CBS from 1977-1983. Judd then landed on another hit television show, called "Dear John". His third success starring in another top rated TV show on CBS called "NUMB3RS", where he played the father of two brothers, an FBI agent and a mathematician who solve crimes together using the latest mathematical techniques.  Alex thanks any and every-one for any support, constructive criticism, money, time, energy and other human blessings he has received throughout his crazy life. Our sincere hope at Key Wins Productions is that by continuing to produce music from the heart, with real instruments played by real people, we can keep the world from fading into “Cosmic Reality TV.” If you agree with us, kindly go to CD BABY and buy one of Alex's 1997 release titled "Naturally", mixed and recorded at The Monkey House in Chicago, featuring all the members from his colossal band, IMPRASIA, a brilliant 17 song collection engineered and produced by BIONIK!

Biography
ven•ture
n.
An undertaking that is dangerous, daring, or of uncertain outcome.
A business enterprise involving some risk in expectation of gain


UPDATE AUGUST 2009: VENTURE HAS OVER 1.5 MILLION ILLEGAL DOWNLOADS OF THEIR MUSIC THROUGH FILE SHARING SITES!

"...Well I can clearly see that you've got what it takes to accomplish your dreams...In the end, it all comes down to the songs. No one in the world can deny a great one."
Mark Tremonti of Creed / Alter Bridge

These are the words that inspired founding member Blake Self to form the band known as VENTURE. After graduating high school, Blake received a hand written letter from his greatest idol. CREED was ruling the airwaves and topping the charts, and their lead guitarist, Mark Tremonti, took the time to write a personal letter to one of his biggest fans.

The wheels were put in motion...the stage was set...VENTURE exploded onto the rock scene from literal obscurity in 3 short years. Their debut CD, THE PRISONER, has already caught the attention of many on radio, and now their live performances are creating quite a stir in the music industry.
" Who are these guys?" is the most often asked question.

Blake Self, Vin Abadie,and Michael Barnes have formed a powerful alliance, and are poised to take their music to the next level. "It's been a great journey so far, and we have so many hurdles to overcome," says lead singer/guitar player Blake Self.

VENTURE was fortunate to work with some amazing producers on their first album. Justin Thomas (Faktion), Brett Hestla (Creed, Dark New Day), and Beau Hill (Ratt, Warrant, Winger, Alice Cooper, Bob Dylon) all have contributed greatly to their success.
"Brett has been instrumental in shaping our sound, and his ideas and suggestions always have a huge impact on our overall sound...he really is an amazing guy!" says Blake.

THE PRISONER was released in September 2007, and their title track, The Prisoner, gained instant praise and acceptance in the radio community, exciting DJ’s on radio and on the world-wide web.

On July 18th, 2007. VENTURE opened for GODSMACK in Dallas TX, and they were received by over 4000 enthusiastic fans! VENTURE was hand picked to open the show, and just two bands were on the bill...VENTURE + GODSMACK!

Recently, VENTURE licensed their music to be featured on upcoming UFC events, Spike TV,Versus Channel, and The Ultimate Fighter Series. WITHOUT A DOUBT was featured in entirety on the UFC 91 DVD... Brock Lesner vs Randy Couture Heavyweight Championship Fight and also featured on the Versus Channel's World Extreme Cagefighting, WEC 36.Their song, IMPOSSIBLE, was featured on the hour long special, Countdown To Ultimate Fight Night 14. The band’s song, GOODBYE, has been licensed in film on the web cast horror series, TV FACE. IMPOSSIBLE has also been featured in SLED HEADS 4 from TAHOE FILMS, an international extreme winter sports series, filmed in Hi-Definition TV. They have continued their inclusion in film with 4 more songs included in the next Tahoe Films project, MOUNTAINS AND MUD 4. Lastly, the band has an informal clothing endorsement with Doctrine Apparel from Los Angeles, CA.

VENTURE'S new song, BITTER, recently won "BEST SINGLE" by the INDEPENDENT SINGER/SONGWRITER ASSOCIATION in 2008.

In July 2008, VENTURE was a Top 10 finalist to join the Van's Warped Tour. Also, VENTURE was a Top 30 finalist to join The Motley Crue Tour, with over 9000 bands entering nationwide.

The band is currently finishing up production on 5 new songs, once again working with the amazing Brett Hestla and Beau Hill.

Look for a new EP launch in January '09!

extra: Garry Moore's discography is a cleaver blend of r&b,pop,jazz,Gospel filled with soul stirring lyrics. There is a message in every song. This is a project that has mass appeal to reach and minister to all age groups. His music crosses all color and cultural lines bringing a message of love, salvation, hope, and deliverance which can only be experienced through a relationship with Jesus Christ. This music project has something for everyone. If you are a lover of christian music with an old school sound, "This is it! driving beats, bone shakin bass, soft sweet melodies, classy horns, and a couple of guitar ripping solo's. Garry Moore's music is the music for you. It will touch and bless the lives of those who are Christian or Non Christian, Centered in praised and worship. But it is also a tool of evangelism with songs like, "Preach The Gospel" and the title track from the album "Paradise". He has a long musical history. A singer, songwriter, musician, and producer. He wrote his first song at age 12, and now has a catalog of over 400 songs. Garry began his musical journey at age 9 when his grandmother formed a gospel quintet of 3 cousins, a friend, and himself. he was the lead voocalist of the young group. being influenced by the "Beatles" he picked up the guitar at age 10. His father also played which inspired him as well. As he grew older he sharpened his guitar skills listening to "Carlos Santana" "Jimi Hendrix" "George Benson" "Al Mckay" and other guitar greats. his gospel influences as a teenager were "Andrae Crouch" "The Mighty Clouds Of Joy" "Rance Alleen" and "Edwin Hawkins".. Other musical influences were "Earth,Wind,& Fire" "The Commodores" " The Isley Brothers" and "The Jacksons".. At age 19,(1979) he formed the group " Garry Moore & New Joy " They recorded their first (45) single the following year (1980) on the H.S.E. Record label in Nashville Tennessee. 4 years later, he and the group recorded their first Album (1984) with a change in the personnel and with a new name "FIRE POWER". The group "Fire Power" opened up for artist like the world renowned Grammy award winning group " The Mighty Clouds Of Joy". The group continued to do concerts and record in the studio during the 80's. in the early 90's the group "Fire Power" disbanded while in the midst of their 2nd studio album and the material was never released. In 1993 Garry answered his call to preach after 20 years trying to pursue a music career. 4 years later (1997) he founded and began Evangelistic Outreach Christian Center. Which the same year he also recorded and released his first solo cd album titled "You're Never Alone" (BUT NEVER RELEASED UNTIL 2011) He then followed up that project 4 years later in 2001 with a cd album titled "Yahweh" which rendered the number 1. radio Hit Single, "Come As You Are". Several songs from the cd received heavy rotation also on college stations. "Finally, after a long hiatus of 8 years from the music scene his 3rd album "Paradise" was released in 2010 on the Tate Music Group label. On June 2nd 2011 "A Blessing For was You" Garry's 4th album was released worldwide on itunes, amazon, napster, Cdbaby and other major digital mp3 stores! (Now currently in the studio working on his May 2012 album)

The soulful, rock band consisting of five young artists, ages ranging from 15 to 22, have been recently making their presence known in their home town of Key Largo, Florida, at such events as the Key Largo Music Festival, the American Cancer Society's Relay For Life, MoradaPalooza, LargoPalooza,Oktoberfest, Winterfest, and more.
Formed by singer/songwriter, Nicholas Petrandis, the band already has local hits, as well as has been receiving local airplay of originals such as "Desert Storm" and "Didn't See It Comin'". The band plans on releasing their first CD before the end of 2011.

extra: . ...... .. .. .. .. .. .. .. .. .. .. ...... .. .. .. .. .. .. .. .. ............View Roksta's EPK.... .. .. ..Music Artist's Name: Roksta .. .. ..Location: Seattle WA / Houston TX .. .. ..Label Name: Unsigned .. .. ..Genre: Hip Hop/Rap .. .. ..Myspace: Myspace.com/RokstaMusik .. .. ..Contact: RokstaMusik@gmail.com .. .. First question we would like to discuss is, where were you born and raised? .. .. [Roksta] Seattle WA .. .. Describe for the readers what your city is like. .. .. [Roksta] I can say in seattle "We make it rain" lol .. The weather can be a little crazy at times but the people ,Nightlife and ladies are wonderful. No matter where I am , I can always call that place home . .. .. How did you get started with hip hop/rap/r&b? .. .. [Roksta] Well, Besides growing up around it ,in the 70s, my dad was in the music industry already in a band called "Parliament Funkadelic", So I have always had a keen Ear for music but the curiosity started when one of my friends started making music from his own home . I experimented with it and let a few people hear what I had to offer and they really enjoyed it . After that, I made my first song "Game right" I really enjoyed making it and I knew Exactly what I wanted to do after that. I was going to pursue my Dream to be the best and Join the best because Music is my passion. .. .. Who are your top inspirational artists? .. .. [Roksta] I would have say Pharrall ,Kanye west, Tpain and lil wayne and ti for Keepin the game fresh and new , and thinking outside the box at all times . I hope I can provide the same quality That they put into there music. .. .. Are you currently working on an album? If so, what is it called? What is the significance of the name? .. .. [Roksta] I plan to have a album out by the end of this year. April 14th 2009 be sure to check out My exclusive "up in the club" Remix on Fenni casino's "The sound of music" album , ITS GANNA BE HOT! .. .. Who is responsible for the beat production and the lyrics behind your music? .. .. [Roksta] For beats, I get alot of them from "White hot productions". And I also Get alot from soundclick.com producers . I think learning to produce my own beats will be the next Project Im going to learn when I have some free time . Shout outs to Nick Altson for helping me on some of my first lyrics ! .. .. Any artists being featured on your album? .. .. [Roksta] As of right now Things are still in the works , but I a guarantee 1 thing , If they aint fire, you wont see em on my album. .. .. Where can readers go to find out more information about you, such as, music, pics, bio, video's, etc? .. .. [Roksta] The most recent up to date info you are going find is going to be kept @ Myspace.com/RokstaMusik. .. .. In 5 years, where do you see yourself amongst the music industry? .. .. [Roksta] Go to www.Billboard.com in 5 years and check the top , Im pretty sure you should see my name there. (lolz) .. .. Any last words or shout outs? .. .. [Roksta] To many people to list , but to my people seatown and fans , Thanks so much for the luv and support and I hope to get on the grammy's one day so I can shout out you guys!! Follow whatchu wanna do in life and dont stop for nobody!! im out.... .. .. This is Abstrakt Formulaz Magazine!! Until next time check out Roksta's music on his myspace page!! Thief of the Night

Music & Lyrics: L’illon

It ain’t that hard to see,

that I’m a woman in need.

For a tender touch of the third degree,

some soft words that will comfort me.

If this seems strange to you,

as you stand without a clue.

Lean in and I’ll whisper it to you,

I’ll reveal some of my hidden truths.

But before I do, I’ve got to ask you….you

Chorus:

Are you the thief of the night,
who will steal my heart and soul?

After you’ve taken what’s mine,

are you coming back for more?

If you’re the thief in my life,

take off your gloves, unmask yourself.

All that is mine, I’m keeping for myself.

Are you the thief, the thief of the night?

Should you make claims on me,

the price is quite hefty.

With a promise to capture the heart of Pittsburgh, August Ruins has emerged from the Steel City underground armed with motivation, a message, and a melody. Founded in May of 2009 August Ruins has found success with an explosive sound, combining the speed and melody of California punk with the technicality of modern metal. From the beginning the band has found the ability to compromise, collaborate and respect each others own musical backgrounds. August Ruins released their debut self-titled demo in December of 2009, and in August of 2010 released their first EP "The Ghost and the Gasoline". title: Solitude
extra:
NYC collective Automatic Children sound a little bit like every cool rock band your older sibling or somewhat friendly record store clerk told you about growing up, thrown into a blender and spit out, creating an entirely potent blend of upbeat, guitar-driven pop.

On their latest 7" Johnny/Now You Know, loud hooks recall Surfer Rosa-era Pixies, while the high-registered vocal delivery of Adam Lippman echoes The Get Up Kids, matched with the world/weary smarts of Paul Westerberg. Influences aside, the simple fact is that Automatic Children are a rock band, streamlined to the basics, who have taken the best of the best and reflected it back in their own way, creating music for discerning fans who are too old to care about trends and like their rock lean, fun, and unpretentious.

Rounded out with Ed Vail (bass/backing vocals) and Kevin Letsch (drums) Automatic Children is at heart the combined songwriting efforts of Adam Lippman and Crista Giuliani. The two met when Adam auditioned Crista to sing and play backup in his solo band in 2006. Once the connection was made and the chemistry and mutual influences obvious after a few shows, the decision to form a proper band was solidified and the rest is history.

"The music is based on our lives, and our experiences, with a little bit of politics thrown in," explains Lippman. Adds Crista, "I think with multiple songwriters, you get a very diverse sound. I think it's good to have different songs for different moods. Who would want to eat the same thing every night for dinner? "
